Dawanal Rakshak:
The "Dawanal Rakshak" system is designed to efficiently manage and combat forest fires using a combination of technology-driven solutions.
The system integrates surveillance cameras, water pumps, humidity sensors, and automated notifications to detect and respond to forest fires in their early stages.
Using technologies such as machine learning and automation ensures rapid, efficient, and cost-effective management.

Has been pitched at IIT Bombay in January 2024.
